<!doctype html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">

    <!-- Always force latest IE rendering engine or request Chrome Frame -->
    <meta content="IE=edge,chrome=1" http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <!-- Use title if it's in the page YAML frontmatter -->
    <title><%= current_page.data.title || "Practical Color Theory" %></title>

    <script src="https://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/2.2.0/jquery.min.js"></script>
    <%= stylesheet_link_tag "red" %>
    <%= javascript_include_tag  "all" %>
</head>
<header>
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Practical Color Theory<br> for People Who Code</h1>
        <h2>Pick your call to action color!</h2>
        <%= partial "partials/color-swatches" %>
        <a href="#start" class="cta-button">Let's get started!</a>
    </div>
    <h3>Natalya Shelburne
        <br>
        <a href="https://twitter.com/natalyathree">@natalyathree</a>
    </h3>
</header>
<body class="<%= page_classes %>">
    <div class="hero">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="half">
                <h1>What is this & why should I listen to you?</h1>

                <p>Hi! I'm Natalya! <img src="images/tally-pic.jpg" class="profile-picture" title="natalya-profile" description="self portrait">I'm a software engineer, a teacher, and a classically trained fine artist.</p>
                <p>This is a demo of my functions for a complementary color scheme - pick any color on the color wheel and the functions will make sure that the scheme will still work! ðŸŽ¨
                </p>
                <p>I have a degree in Studio Art, a bachelor's in Developmental Psychology, and a master's degree in Creativity and Talent Development. I have mixed gallons and gallons of paint and taught many people how to paint, draw, and grow their creativity before making front end development my full time pursuit.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="half">
                <h1>Prerequisites</h1>
            </p>
            <h4>Completely new to this? Check out these resources first:</h4>
            <ul class="text-list-item-box">
                <li><a href="http://www.w3.org/TR/css3-color/#hsl-color">CSS Color Module Level 3: HSL</a></li>
                <li><a href="http://hslpicker.com/">Most Excellent HSL color picker</a></li>
                <li><a href="http://jackiebalzer.com/color">Interactive Sass Color Functions</a></li>
                <li><a href="http://sass-lang.com/documentation/Sass/Script/Functions.html#hsla-instance_method">Read the Sass-lang Docs</a></li>
            </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <%= yield %>
    </body>
</html>
